attachments.title: #70 Add movie log
attachments.text:
Front end implementation for movie log feature:

• Displays Movie Log on profile page (I copy/pasted Merve's formatting for consistency)
• 'Rate and Log' button displayed beneath each item on the watchlist lets the user rate and log movies they've watched, with the option to remove from watchlist when they submit the rating
• Star rating for each movie displays on log entry, with option to change the rating by clicking the stars
• Movie log entries include delete button to remove unwanted entries

A couple cosmetic changes:

• Played around with spacing on front page (this was a while ago and someone else's edits may have made it irrelevant by now)
• Updated tagline from "Spend your time watching" to "Less time scrolling, more time watching" - do we like this?

TO DO: Changes are saving to the database and are visible when you refresh the page, but I'm not sure how to get the changes to display/get the watchlist and log sections to re-render without fully refreshing the page. Can someone help with this?
